1
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:39,640
This photo is too blurry.

2
00:01:40,039 --> 00:01:41,120
I can't be sure,

3
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:43,120
but in my impression,

4
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:46,280
Brigade Commander Zhang was very tall,

5
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:48,210
with straight and thick eyebrows,

6
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:49,810
and a straight nose.

7
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:52,920
While we were fleeing,

8
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,320
we lost some luggage.

9
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:56,320
This is the only photo

10
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:59,120
I have left of my husband.

11
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,360
But his unit

12
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:03,970
belonged to the 130th Army,

13
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,730
187th Division, 87th Brigade.

14
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:10,360
I remember when Brigade Commander Zhang was brought in,

15
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:12,360
his clothes were torn to pieces.

16
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:14,490
I didn't see his unit designation.

17
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:16,079
The only thing I am sure of

18
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:17,760
is that in early September,

19
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:19,920
he was sent from the direction of Luodian.

20
00:02:19,920 --> 00:02:21,920
The medics who brought him over said

21
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:25,130
his entire brigade was almost completely wiped out.

22
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:27,360
Brigade Commander Zhang was leading a suicide squad

23
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:28,560
to meet reinforcements when

24
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,079
they were surrounded by the Japanese.

25
00:02:30,079 --> 00:02:32,560
He was injured when they finally broke through.

26
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,320
The last place my husband fought

27
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:36,079
was in Liu Town near Luodian.

28
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,840
And the timeline matches.

29
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:39,800
Brother Xiaoyun,

30
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:41,840
do you have any other impression

31
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,960
of this Brigade Commander Zhang?

32
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:45,960
I remember him very well.

33
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:48,000
He is the person I will

34
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:50,280
never forget in my life.

35
00:02:51,040 --> 00:02:53,560
When we arranged the surgery for Brigade Commander Zhang,

36
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:54,690
it was late at night.

37
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:56,920
Brigade Commander Zhang was severely injured.

38
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:58,560
Below his left knee,

39
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:00,860
the bones, blood vessels, and nerves

40
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:02,720
were all severed by shrapnel.

41
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:04,520
The frontline medics

42
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:07,400
only tied his thigh to stop the bleeding.

43
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:09,400
Because bringing him here

44
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,730
was delayed for so long,

45
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:12,290
when I examined him,

46
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:14,040
the wound had turned black

47
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,160
and necrotic.

48
00:03:16,720 --> 00:03:18,920
Amputation was the only option.

49
00:03:20,079 --> 00:03:22,210
I remember when I was operating on him,

50
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:26,120
there was a soldier outside the tent

51
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,660
constantly begging me

52
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:29,320
to save

53
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:32,240
his squad leader who blew up a Japanese tank...

54
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:33,640
We were operating on him.

55
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:37,120
But due to the severe shortage of medicine,

56
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:39,160
only officers above the rank of lieutenant

57
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:41,090
were qualified to use anesthesia.

58
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:42,800
When we were preparing to inject

59
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:45,130
anesthesia for Brigade Commander Zhang,

60
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:47,400
he suddenly said to me,

61
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:50,120
"I've lost a leg,

62
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:53,450
and I can never return to the battlefield.

63
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,640
Give my anesthesia

64
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:58,079
to the brother next door."

65
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,600
We all tried to persuade him,

66
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:03,520
but he insisted.

67
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:07,440
We had to respect his choice.

68
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:09,360
You know what?

69
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:11,970
An amputation without anesthesia

70
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,480
is beyond imagination.

71
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:16,760
We tied a towel

72
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:19,579
around Brigade Commander Zhang's mouth

73
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:22,680
to prevent him from biting himself in pain,

74
00:04:23,480 --> 00:04:25,560
and then firmly fixed his limbs and shoulders

75
00:04:25,560 --> 00:04:27,200
to the bed.

76
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:30,080
Guan Yu scraping poison off his bone

77
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:31,640
is just a legend.

78
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:33,640
But that night,

79
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:35,360
I saw a man

80
00:04:37,159 --> 00:04:38,720
made of iron.

81
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:40,800
Did he

82
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,200
survive the surgery?

83
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:47,400
He survived.

84
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:51,280
The surgery lasted over an hour,

85
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:53,000
which was a miracle.

86
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,120
For a few days after the surgery,

87
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:57,040
he was given special care.

88
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:59,420
He recovered well the first few days.

89
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:01,320
Was it the few days when I went to the hospital

90
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:03,880
to deliver medicines and supplies?

91
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:04,680
Yes.

92
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:07,480
But

93
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:10,480
a week after those few days,

94
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:14,360
Brigade Commander Zhang had a postoperative infection,

95
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:16,880
which caused visceral complications.

96
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:18,210
The physical toll of

97
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:20,700
the amputation was too great.

98
00:05:21,640 --> 00:05:24,520
He didn't make it through.

99
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:27,840
We tried our best to save him.

100
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:29,040
But

101
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:32,080
he still passed away.

102
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:37,159
Madam Zhang, I'm sorry.

103
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:40,320
I did my best.

104
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:54,600
First of all, thank you, Dr. Chen,

105
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:57,920
for telling me this.

106
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:00,280
Thank you very much.

107
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:08,160
Madam Zhang, your husband

108
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:11,160
is the man I admire most in my life.

109
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:33,420
Please have a seat.

110
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:47,880
Hurry up.

111
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:10,200
Mr. Fujita.

112
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:14,000
My client, Mr. Zhang Ruxian,

113
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:16,760
expresses his deep apologies

114
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:19,240
and sincerely apologizes to you.

115
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,000
Apologies?

116
00:07:24,600 --> 00:07:26,280
I didn't see that.

117
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:37,640
Mr. Fujita.

118
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:41,520
My father has been tortured into a stupor.

119
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,159
In front of him,

120
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,300
I represent him

121
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:46,840
to express my sincere apologies to you.

122
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:49,960
This letter was dictated by my father.

123
00:07:50,280 --> 00:07:53,240
Lawyer Wu wrote it down word by word.

124
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:54,159
Yes.

125
00:07:58,120 --> 00:08:00,320
Have him read it to me.

126
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,880
My father's eyesight is failing.

127
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,080
He can't see clearly.

128
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:07,360
Then you read it.

129
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:10,160
You read a sentence, and he repeats it.

130
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:12,840
He insulted my character for no reason.

131
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:16,120
He insulted the dignity of the great Japanese Empire.

132
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:19,800
I want the sincerity of his apology.

133
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:23,960
Mr. Fujita.

134
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:26,000
I understand your demands.

135
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:26,840
Look,

136
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,480
can I talk to my client

137
00:08:29,280 --> 00:08:30,280
for a moment?

138
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:37,720
I need these two to help me

139
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:39,440
talk to the client.

140
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:52,920
Lawyer Wu.

141
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:55,360
He has to suffer this.

142
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:57,480
This letter must be read.

143
00:08:57,680 --> 00:08:59,440
But how can my father read it like this?

144
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:00,440
Leave it to me.

145
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:01,540
Let's talk inside.

146
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:03,800
Father.

147
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:05,160
Father.

148
00:09:06,360 --> 00:09:07,120
Master.

149
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,060
Look who's here to see you.

150
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:10,400
Look.

151
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,170
Yueming, Yue...

152
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:14,080
My little Yueming.

153
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:15,820
Yueming is here to see you.

154
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:17,240
Master.

155
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:21,520
Do you know where this is?

156
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:24,360
Do you know how you got here?

157
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,000
Master.

158
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:32,080
Do you remember what happened?

159
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:33,280
What?

160
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:36,360
Let's follow the old rules.

161
00:09:36,360 --> 00:09:37,690
No matter what they say,

162
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:39,160
as soon as I pull you,

163
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:40,640
you just say yes.

164
00:09:40,720 --> 00:09:42,000
Yes, it is.

165
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:51,360
Ms. Ding, come.

166
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,720
Mr. Fujita, look.

167
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:22,280
Given my client's health condition,

168
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:23,770
could you please

169
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:27,480
let Ms. Ding fully represent him

170
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:29,320
to read this apology letter?

171
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:30,800
Is that okay?

172
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,400
What about his attitude?

173
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:34,900
He will show his attitude.

174
00:11:09,760 --> 00:11:12,480
A letter to a certain gentleman from Japan,

175
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:14,520
presented to Mr. Fujita.

176
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:16,560
I can't hear you.

177
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,520
Yes, it is.

178
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:29,160
For Mr. Fujita's perusal.

179
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:31,720
I am old and conservative,

180
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,660
fond of learning and wine.

181
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:35,920
I am straightforward and narrow-minded,

182
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:37,850
and often realize things too late.

183
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:40,800
You are living in our country,

184
00:11:41,160 --> 00:11:42,420
admiring our culture.

185
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:45,320
Invited to my home,

186
00:11:46,040 --> 00:11:48,080
I should have hosted you with wine

187
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:50,140
and treated you as a bosom friend.

188
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:54,240
But I lost control of my emotions

189
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:57,040
and ruined my reputation.

190
00:11:59,120 --> 00:12:00,320
That's how it is.

191
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:17,000
The way of poetry, books, rites, and music

192
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:19,360
is to maintain peace.

193
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:23,040
When two countries go to war,

194
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:25,760
it is the politicians' doing.

195
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:30,760
We scholars are all deeply pained.

196
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:34,240
You are a man of noble character

197
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:37,740
and treat your neighbors with kindness.

198
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:41,520
I vented my personal anger on my fellow writers,

199
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:43,610
making a grave mistake,

200
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:46,080
and I regret it deeply.

201
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:50,880
I hope you can be magnanimous and forgive me.

202
00:12:51,040 --> 00:12:55,520
From the old man in Shanghai, Zhang Ruxian.

203
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,040
Yujiao.

204
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:05,880
Father.

205
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:07,840
What did you say

206
00:13:09,040 --> 00:13:10,570
in your last two sentences?

207
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:27,000
I regret it deeply.

208
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:34,240
I hope you can be magnanimous and forgive me.

209
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:38,760
I heard what you said.

210
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:40,680
Let him speak.

211
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:44,920
That's how it is.

212
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:47,000
That's how it is.

213
00:13:50,360 --> 00:13:52,120
That's how it is.

214
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:05,720
It's not like that.

215
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:16,560
How dare you wear Chinese clothes!

216
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:18,480
The vast Huaxia

217
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:21,200
is the country of elegant clothing.

218
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:26,640
The beauty of clothes is called Hua,

219
00:14:27,160 --> 00:14:30,600
and the greatness of rites is called Xia.

220
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:33,240
A tiny, insignificant country like you,

221
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:34,720
you beast!

222
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:36,520
Do you deserve this?

223
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:39,520
How absurd!

224
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:42,000
He has no intention of apologizing at all.

225
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:42,840
Mr. Fujita.

226
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:44,800
Misunderstanding. This must be a misunderstanding.

227
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:45,560
Calm down.

228
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:46,480
Calm down.

229
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:48,000
He is so ungrateful.

230
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:49,800
Then let him go to the Gendarmerie

231
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:51,600
and show off his stubbornness.

232
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:53,400
You remember this, bastard!

233
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:54,640
Mr. Fujita.

234
00:14:54,680 --> 00:14:55,400
Mr. Fujita.

235
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:58,160
Mr. Fujita.

236
00:14:59,200 --> 00:14:59,920
Mr. Fujita.

237
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:01,280
It's a misunderstanding.

238
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:02,080
Mr. Fujita.

239
00:15:04,360 --> 00:15:05,960
Go back to your cell.

240
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:07,000
Misunderstanding. Mr. Fujita.

241
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,160
Sir, look,

242
00:15:09,240 --> 00:15:10,680
our family is finally together.

243
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:12,210
It's not easy for us to talk.

244
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:14,000
Could you please do us a favor?

245
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:15,600
Father.

246
00:15:15,640 --> 00:15:16,480
No.

247
00:15:16,560 --> 00:15:17,920
It's what I should do, brother.

248
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:19,650
It's what I should do, brother.

249
00:15:20,040 --> 00:15:21,240
It's what I should do.

250
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:23,680
Hurry up.

251
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:25,360
Yujiao,

252
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:32,040
did you really write this letter?

253
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:38,600
Well done.

254
00:15:41,280 --> 00:15:42,540
Beautifully written.

255
00:15:43,280 --> 00:15:45,920
Every word is a gem.

256
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:48,080
When you wrote it,

257
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:53,280
didn't you think of Yunkui?

258
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:54,920
What are you doing? Are you crazy?

259
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:56,600
Sir!

260
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:00,280
Father.

261
00:16:02,520 --> 00:16:07,920
It's because I think of Yunkui all the time.

262
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:10,520
Yunkui is gone.

263
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:14,680
I have to keep you alive.

264
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:17,280
Do I have to surrender to stay alive?

265
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:19,840
Yunkui didn't surrender.

266
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:21,560
He died.

267
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,800
But I didn't expect

268
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:27,640
you to do such a thing.

269
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:28,640
Master,

270
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:31,600
how could you say that about Madam?

271
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:33,600
When Madam wrote this letter,

272
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:35,840
every word tore at her heart.

273
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:38,160
If I knew how to read,

274
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:40,600
I would have read it for her.

275
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:43,240
If you don't think for yourself,

276
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:45,580
you should think for Yueming.

277
00:16:45,600 --> 00:16:48,240
Think of your grandson!

278
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:12,079
For the ideal that I hold dear to my heart,

279
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:17,200
I'd not regret a thousand times to die.

280
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:22,119
I remember when Yunkui was little,

281
00:17:22,720 --> 00:17:25,040
I told him about Qu Yuan.

282
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:31,080
He asked me 21 times a day who Qu Yuan was,

283
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:36,480
and why Minister Qu Yuan drowned himself in the river.

284
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:41,200
And I explained it to him 21 times.

285
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:43,640
After Yunkui listened,

286
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:46,920
he cried loudly.

287
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,520
He understood it.

288
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:50,280
He got it.

289
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:54,880
I told him that dying without regrets

290
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:58,920
is actually a simple sentence.

291
00:18:01,160 --> 00:18:05,400
Some people, for a cause,

292
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:07,960
dare to fight,

293
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:09,600
dare to bleed,

294
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:12,090
dare to sacrifice their lives.

295
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:16,520
That's how my grandfather taught my father.

296
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:19,880
And my father taught me the same way.

297
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,920
I taught Yunkui the same way.

298
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:24,680
Yujiao,

299
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:29,160
how I wish you would teach Yueming the same way.

300
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:32,680
I cannot apologize.

301
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:36,080
If I apologize to them,

302
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:38,400
I wouldn't be me anymore.

303
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:42,800
Yunkui was in his prime.

304
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:45,480
He practiced this belief,

305
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:47,480
and died a worthy death.

306
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:49,760
I am his father.

307
00:18:50,360 --> 00:18:52,040
I can't lose to him.

308
00:18:52,760 --> 00:18:53,680
I can't.

309
00:18:54,760 --> 00:18:57,200
This head cannot bow.

310
00:18:57,800 --> 00:18:59,800
This waist cannot bend.

311
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:01,240
Cannot.

312
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:06,240
Yujiao.

313
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:11,880
Go.

314
00:19:13,680 --> 00:19:14,520
Go.

315
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:17,320
As for my matters,

316
00:19:18,280 --> 00:19:20,080
don't bother anymore.

317
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:22,280
Don't.

318
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:39,880
Let's go.

319
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:43,880
Stop looking. Let's hurry up and leave.

320
00:19:43,880 --> 00:19:44,800
Okay.

321
00:19:46,320 --> 00:19:47,000
Hurry.

322
00:19:57,360 --> 00:19:57,880
Let's go quickly.

323
00:19:57,880 --> 00:19:58,560
Go.

324
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:13,840
Wanfu.

325
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:16,040
Was I wrong?

326
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:19,170
How could you be wrong for saving someone?

327
00:20:19,280 --> 00:20:22,480
If anyone is to blame, it's Master for being too stubborn.

328
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:24,440
Back to Shanghai.

329
00:20:24,920 --> 00:20:25,960
Was I wrong?

330
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:29,610
You and Master share the same problem.

331
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:32,000
You're too stubborn.

332
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:34,400
You'd rather suffer than lose face.

333
00:20:35,600 --> 00:20:36,800
If you ask me, reading a letter

334
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:38,240
is no big deal.

335
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:40,600
Staying alive is the most important thing.

336
00:20:40,600 --> 00:20:41,400
No.

337
00:20:42,080 --> 00:20:44,160
I shouldn't have returned to Shanghai.

338
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:45,360
If I had gone to Wuhan,

339
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:47,400
Master would be fine.

340
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:50,200
Mrs. Liu would also be alive and well.

341
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:51,400
Madam, madam, madam.

342
00:20:51,440 --> 00:20:53,440
You must not be too hard on yourself.

343
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:54,080
Think about it.

344
00:20:54,080 --> 00:20:55,240
If we hadn't come to Shanghai,

345
00:20:55,240 --> 00:20:57,280
we would all have boarded the Meiyun to Wuhan.

346
00:20:57,280 --> 00:20:58,360
When the Meiyun was bombed,

347
00:20:58,360 --> 00:21:00,490
wouldn't we all have died in the river?

348
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:05,800
That's right.

349
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:08,360
Otherwise, even Yueming would be gone.

350
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:15,800
Filled with endless regret.

351
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:17,200
Asking for forgiveness?

352
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:18,840
Forgive my ass!

353
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:19,880
Don't tear it.

354
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:22,320
Keep it to teach Yueming.

355
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:52,640
Are you from Lutai Restaurant?

356
00:21:52,640 --> 00:21:53,240
Yes.

357
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:55,380
I'm here to deliver Baozi to Mr. Tian.

358
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:56,340
Give them to me.

359
00:21:58,040 --> 00:22:00,840
Please tell Mr. Tian to eat them while they're hot.

360
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:02,320
Thank you.

361
00:22:05,280 --> 00:22:06,480
I sent someone to Pétain Police Station

362
00:22:06,480 --> 00:22:07,480
to ask Officer Wang.

363
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:08,800
There is an old gentleman,

364
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:11,080
whose relatives invited the Japanese to his home as guests.

365
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:11,880
The old gentleman got angry,

366
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:13,200
and kicked them out directly.

367
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:14,920
He was framed as an Anti-Japanese element.

368
00:22:14,920 --> 00:22:15,980
It's not a big deal.

369
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:18,900
The Japanese just wants him to apologize in person.

370
00:22:19,280 --> 00:22:20,960
His relatives wrote an apology letter,

371
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:22,000
but he scolded them

372
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,130
and made a big scene.

373
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:24,160
People at the police station

374
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:25,960
say the Old Master must be crazy.

375
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:28,930
He recites 'Li Sao' loudly in prison all day long.

376
00:22:29,680 --> 00:22:31,560
Who is that cook?

377
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:33,760
I sent someone to check on him too.

378
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:34,800
He has no background.

379
00:22:34,800 --> 00:22:37,200
He just focuses on saving his crazy father.

380
00:22:37,480 --> 00:22:39,880
The cook's father recites 'Li Sao'?

381
00:22:40,120 --> 00:22:42,160
That's what the people at the police station said.

382
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:43,400
Come, Brother Qi.

383
00:22:45,760 --> 00:22:46,690
Hold this for me.

384
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:47,960
Come on.

385
00:22:49,320 --> 00:22:50,180
Give me a smile.

386
00:22:52,480 --> 00:22:53,200
Smile.

387
00:22:58,280 --> 00:22:59,560
I just love your smile.

388
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:00,760
Interesting.

389
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:22,600
Everyone's busy.

390
00:23:23,120 --> 00:23:23,920
Boss.

391
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:28,720
What meat is this?

392
00:23:29,080 --> 00:23:29,760
Beef.

393
00:23:30,120 --> 00:23:32,320
Look, a newly developed Baozi filling.

394
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:35,560
I plan to make the Seven Delicacies of Lanling.

395
00:23:40,280 --> 00:23:42,400
I've never even heard of the Seven Delicacies of Lanling.

396
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:43,660
You're just bragging.

397
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:44,360
Boss,

398
00:23:44,480 --> 00:23:47,480
do you know these seven delicacies or eight views

399
00:23:47,560 --> 00:23:48,840
are all gimmicks?

400
00:23:49,120 --> 00:23:51,600
The main thing is this Baozi filling.

401
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:52,560
Come.

402
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:53,080
Try it.

403
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:53,720
Go away.

404
00:23:53,960 --> 00:23:55,090
Keep developing it.

405
00:23:58,800 --> 00:24:01,360
Which table ordered the sea cucumber and abalone?

406
00:24:01,360 --> 00:24:01,960
No one ordered them.

407
00:24:01,960 --> 00:24:03,620
Wanfu is using them for Baozi.

408
00:24:03,640 --> 00:24:04,480
For Baozi?

409
00:24:05,160 --> 00:24:05,880
Wanfu!

410
00:24:05,960 --> 00:24:08,080
Who let you use sea cucumber and abalone for Baozi?

411
00:24:08,080 --> 00:24:09,140
Isn't this a waste?

412
00:24:09,240 --> 00:24:10,080
Boss.

413
00:24:11,080 --> 00:24:13,080
Nothing ventured, nothing gained.

414
00:24:13,160 --> 00:24:14,120
You sell pancakes every day,

415
00:24:14,120 --> 00:24:15,440
how much money can you earn?

416
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:18,080
If making Baozi with sea cucumber and abalone can earn money,

417
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:19,610
ask them if they believe it.

418
00:24:24,760 --> 00:24:26,280
Boss, this...

419
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:28,410
If these things lose money,

420
00:24:28,520 --> 00:24:30,250
you can deduct it from my wages.

421
00:24:30,440 --> 00:24:31,560
You only make a few coins a month.

422
00:24:31,560 --> 00:24:32,560
Is it enough to deduct?

423
00:24:32,560 --> 00:24:33,120
Besides,

424
00:24:33,200 --> 00:24:35,200
the money for the ten baskets of Baozi you owe me hasn't been fully deducted yet.

425
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:36,930
You're bringing this up again.

426
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:37,880
Boss,

427
00:24:38,120 --> 00:24:39,760
I haven't just been working for you for a day or two.

428
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:41,360
I'll work for you for the rest of my life.

429
00:24:41,360 --> 00:24:42,640
Just deduct it slowly.

430
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:44,080
You can't ruin my whole life.

431
00:24:44,080 --> 00:24:46,120
I'm not ruining you, Boss.

432
00:24:46,320 --> 00:24:48,120
I'm just doing this for Lutai.

433
00:25:11,960 --> 00:25:12,640
Wanfu.

434
00:25:13,840 --> 00:25:14,680
You scared me.

435
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:16,280
You scared me.

436
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:20,730
Why are you here?

437
00:25:20,880 --> 00:25:21,480
These past few days,

438
00:25:21,480 --> 00:25:23,680
Zhang Yunqi and his wife aren't at home.

439
00:25:23,840 --> 00:25:25,570
I don't know what they're up to,

440
00:25:25,920 --> 00:25:27,580
but I've been feeling uneasy.

441
00:25:27,880 --> 00:25:29,010
Then sit for a while.

442
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:31,560
I can't sit.

443
00:25:34,320 --> 00:25:36,240
How are your baozi today?

444
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:38,200
Don't mention it.

445
00:25:38,880 --> 00:25:40,080
I'm worried to death.

446
00:25:40,480 --> 00:25:43,140
I've been making baozi for Mr. Tian for six days.

447
00:25:43,560 --> 00:25:44,320
You know,

448
00:25:44,440 --> 00:25:46,170
Mr. Tian has eaten everything.

449
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:47,340
These six days,

450
00:25:47,640 --> 00:25:49,480
I've made everything that flies in the sky,

451
00:25:49,480 --> 00:25:50,200
swims in the water,

452
00:25:50,200 --> 00:25:51,400
and jumps on the grass.

453
00:25:51,400 --> 00:25:52,880
Things that can be made, things that can't,

454
00:25:52,880 --> 00:25:53,560
things I want to make,

455
00:25:53,560 --> 00:25:55,000
things I can think of, things I can't,

456
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:56,060
I've made them all.

457
00:25:58,160 --> 00:25:59,490
I'm really out of ideas.

458
00:26:01,480 --> 00:26:02,360
Help me think.

459
00:26:06,560 --> 00:26:07,560
I don't know.

460
00:26:07,720 --> 00:26:08,600
Just think,

461
00:26:08,920 --> 00:26:10,920
you've been eating baozi for six days.

462
00:26:10,920 --> 00:26:11,980
On the seventh day,

463
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,600
what filling would you want?

464
00:26:14,440 --> 00:26:16,800
Eating baozi for six days straight?

465
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:21,280
Then I want egg drop soup.

466
00:26:22,320 --> 00:26:23,720
Are you kidding me?

467
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:25,600
I'm not kidding. I'm serious.

468
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:26,680
He wants to eat baozi.

469
00:26:26,680 --> 00:26:28,340
Why would he eat egg drop soup?

470
00:26:29,640 --> 00:26:31,000
Right now, this egg drop soup

471
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:32,460
can't even cool my temper.

472
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:33,920
Didn't you ask me?

473
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:37,440
We're not eating it.

474
00:26:37,440 --> 00:26:39,080
Mr. Tian's taste...

475
00:26:39,600 --> 00:26:40,530
What should I do?

476
00:26:40,760 --> 00:26:42,490
What other fillings are there?

477
00:26:42,760 --> 00:26:43,620
Dough filling.

478
00:26:45,560 --> 00:26:46,420
Dough filling.

479
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:50,460
Isn't that just steamed buns?

480
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:51,880
I think,

481
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:53,920
even though Mr. Tian agreed with you

482
00:26:53,920 --> 00:26:55,180
on seven days of baozi,

483
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:57,200
he might not be after your baozi.

484
00:26:57,320 --> 00:26:58,320
Then what is he after?

485
00:26:58,320 --> 00:26:59,720
He's after your sincerity.

486
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:01,800
Since you can't think of anything anyway,

487
00:27:01,800 --> 00:27:03,200
you might as well just

488
00:27:03,240 --> 00:27:05,240
make a steamer of sincere steamed buns.

489
00:27:05,240 --> 00:27:07,400
They might not be any less delicious than baozi.

490
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:09,520
No, you're talking in riddles.

491
00:27:09,560 --> 00:27:11,420
Why do you sound like Blind Huang?

492
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:12,560
But I feel

493
00:27:14,120 --> 00:27:15,520
like it makes some sense.

494
00:27:15,560 --> 00:27:16,640
Who is Blind Huang?

495
00:27:17,320 --> 00:27:18,320
A fortune teller.

496
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:19,500
Don't mind him.

497
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:21,650
Since we've already promised,

498
00:27:21,680 --> 00:27:23,200
we definitely can't break our word.

499
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:24,800
Just do it with your heart.

500
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:26,920
Okay.

501
00:27:27,400 --> 00:27:28,800
We'll make steamed buns.

502
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:29,680
I trust you.

503
00:27:35,800 --> 00:27:36,640
Come here.

504
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:50,360
Good girl.

505
00:27:50,840 --> 00:27:51,970
Wait for mommy a bit.

506
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:06,800
Come on.

507
00:28:08,480 --> 00:28:09,410
What should I do?

508
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:11,400
Pour this flour into the vat.

509
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:12,680
All of it?

510
00:28:12,760 --> 00:28:13,240
Yes, all of it.

511
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:13,840
Okay.

512
00:28:21,920 --> 00:28:22,680
And then?

513
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:26,360
Put a little salt in this big bowl.

514
00:28:27,760 --> 00:28:28,520
How much?

515
00:28:28,680 --> 00:28:29,480
Just a little.

516
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:31,450
Is it enough?

517
00:28:32,280 --> 00:28:33,000
Too little.

518
00:28:37,120 --> 00:28:38,180
What are you doing?

519
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:40,720
Are you trying to salt Mr. Tian to death?

520
00:28:40,720 --> 00:28:41,650
That's too much.

521
00:28:41,840 --> 00:28:43,100
It's fine, let me do it.

522
00:28:54,320 --> 00:28:55,640
This is sourdough starter.

523
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:57,320
I'll knead it, you won't do it evenly.

524
00:28:57,320 --> 00:28:58,320
Then what can I do?

525
00:28:59,200 --> 00:29:00,600
Add sugar. You add sugar.

526
00:29:03,560 --> 00:29:04,360
How much?

527
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:05,760
A handful.

528
00:29:10,760 --> 00:29:11,400
Let me see.

529
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:15,960
A little less.

530
00:29:17,080 --> 00:29:17,720
Okay.

531
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:18,680
Put it in.

532
00:29:19,800 --> 00:29:22,040
Mix the sugar, flour, and salt evenly.

533
00:29:23,920 --> 00:29:25,400
Bring this water over.

534
00:29:25,560 --> 00:29:26,490
Pour it in for me.

535
00:29:27,040 --> 00:29:27,920
I'll pour when you say so.

536
00:29:27,920 --> 00:29:29,040
And stop when you say stop.

537
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:29,600
Okay.

538
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:31,200
Pour.

539
00:29:31,800 --> 00:29:32,360
Stop.

540
00:29:34,640 --> 00:29:35,120
Pour.

541
00:29:36,440 --> 00:29:38,160
Why don't you try?

542
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:39,200
Sure.

543
00:29:40,680 --> 00:29:42,520
The harder you knead, the chewier it gets.

544
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:44,720
The chewier it is, the better the texture.

545
00:29:44,720 --> 00:29:45,840
Really?

546
00:29:48,600 --> 00:29:50,320
Qi, why are you here?

547
00:29:54,160 --> 00:29:54,920
Sorry.

548
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:56,320
Is Mr. Tian getting impatient?

549
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:57,560
Our Baozi isn't ready yet.

550
00:29:57,560 --> 00:29:58,640
Don't mention Baozi anymore.

551
00:29:58,640 --> 00:30:00,640
Mr. Tian will throw up if he eats any more.

552
00:30:00,640 --> 00:30:03,440
You need to go to Pétain Police Station right away.

553
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:06,800
Me?

554
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:08,720
What happened to my father?

555
00:30:08,720 --> 00:30:10,120
Mr. Tian made two calls.

556
00:30:10,560 --> 00:30:12,200
The police station just replied.

557
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:13,360
They arranged his release.

558
00:30:13,360 --> 00:30:14,690
Hurry up and pick him up.

559
00:30:18,280 --> 00:30:19,160
Thank Mr. Tian for me.

560
00:30:19,160 --> 00:30:20,080
Thank you, Qi.

561
00:30:21,680 --> 00:30:22,740
Don't give me that.

562
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:26,280
Qi.

563
00:30:27,320 --> 00:30:28,720
I can't thank you enough.

564
00:30:35,840 --> 00:30:37,300
I'll wait for you outside.

565
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:44,880
Let's go.

566
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:45,480
Let's go.

567
00:30:50,960 --> 00:30:52,690
We are going to pick up grandpa.

568
00:30:54,520 --> 00:30:55,200
Let's go.

569
00:30:55,240 --> 00:30:56,640
Apron, apron.

570
00:31:41,840 --> 00:31:43,120
Th-thank you, Sir.

571
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:44,600
Madam.

572
00:32:03,600 --> 00:32:04,200
Father.

573
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:06,120
Father.

574
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:17,280
We're going home.

575
00:32:20,320 --> 00:32:20,980
Going home.

576
